    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Debouncing was discussed in #776 and could be solved via #817.\n\nAlso I think typing with urlSync already updates the URL with `replaceState` rather than `pushState` which eliminates the back button problem. See http://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/examples/media where when you type fast this pushes only a single state in the browser history which gets replaced on subsequent characters. Only after you stop typing for a moment it would push the next characters in a new state.\n",
    "created_at": "2016-02-04T20:55:02Z",
